Lizabeth H. Zlatkus  Independent Director, Boston Private Financial Holdings, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships58$120,000
Background

		Ms. Lizabeth H. Zlatkus, also known as Liz, served as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of Hartford Life, Inc. until October 2011. Ms. Zlatkus has spent 28 years with The Hartford Financial Services Group where she held many executive leadership positions. Prior to joining Hartford, she was a senior accountant with KPMG. She served as a Co-President, Co-Chief Executive Officer, Executive Vice President, Chief Financial Officer and Chairman of Hartford ... Life Insurance Company. She served as the Chief Financial Officer of The Hartford Financial Services Group Inc. from May 1, 2008 to March 1, 2010 and served as its served as Executive Vice President from June 2007 to December 31, 2011. She served as the Chief Risk Officer of The Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. from October 2009 to December 31, 2011. She served as the President of International Wealth Management and Group Benefits of Hartford Financial Services Group Inc., from February 23, 2006 to May 1, 2008 and served as its Co-Chief Operating Officers of The Hartford's life operations from June 2007 to May 1, 2008. She was named Chief Financial Officer in 2003 and was also given responsibility for actuarial, risk management and Hartford Life's information technology area. During her time as Chief Financial Officer, she led the development of Hartford Life's industry-leading risk management and hedging program. She joined Hartford in 1983 in the property-casualty area. She moved to Hartford Life in 1990 and held a number of positions with increasing responsibility. She joined GBD in 1996 and was promoted to Executive Vice President in 2000. During her years at the helm of GBD, the division had cumulative earnings of 19 percent, a consistent ROE of better than 15 percent and became the number two seller of group disability insurance. She began her professional career at Peat Marwick Mitchell & Co. (now known as KPMG). She has been a Director of Computer Sciences Corp., since August 10, 2016. She has been Non-Executive Director of Indivior PLC since September 01, 2016. Ms. Zlatkus has been a Director of Boston Private Financial Holdings, Inc. and Boston Private Bank & Trust Company since July 1, 2015. She served as an Independent Non-Executive Director of Legal & General Group Plc since December 1, 2013 until August 31, 2016. She served as Director of Hartford Life Insurance Company. She was a member of the Hewlett Packard Financial Services Board of Advisors. She served on the LOMA Board of Directors since 2005. She was recognized by Hillary Clinton for her work supporting the disability community and in 1999, participated as a member of The President’s Committee on Employment of People with Disabilities. She served as the Chair of the Pennsylvania State University Business School Board, Finance Chair of the Connecticut Science Center Trustee Board and is a Trustee of the Connecticut Women’s Hall of Fame. Ms. Zlatkus has also served as a Consultant on acquisition, finance and risk issues and works with universities in a variety of capacities. She was named one of the top 100 women executives by Business Insurance magazine, named to the Women Worth Watching List by the Profiles in Diversity Journal in 2000 and 2006, listed as one of Eight Remarkable Women by the Hartford Business Journal in 2008 and presented with the Community Leader of the Year by the Cystic Fibrosis Foundation’s Connecticut Chapter. She served as Regulatory Chair for the North American Chief Risk Officers Council. She served as a Director of Computer Sciences Corporation until April 1, 2017. Ms. Zlatkus graduated (B.S.) with distinction from The Pennsylvania State University in 1981, was selected as an Alumni Fellow in 2003 and served as the commencement speaker for the business school in 2013.Read Full Background




