Lizabeth Zlatkus
Non-Executive Director


Liz is a qualified financial and risk expert with international experience, having served on the Boards of large public companies in both the UK and the US. She currently serves as a Non-Executive Director on the Board of Boston Private Financial Holdings, Inc., and has experience serving on Audit and Risk Committees. Lizabeth previously served as a Non-Executive Director on the Board of Computer Sciences Corporation, and of Legal & General Group, Plc from December 2013 until August 2016, serving on the Audit, Risk and Nominating Committees.
Lizabeth held a variety of senior roles at The Hartford Financial Services Group during her 28 year tenure from 1983 – 2011, including as Chief Financial Officer and Chief Risk Officer for the firm. In addition, she held the role of Co-President, Hartford Life Insurance Companies, where she built highly engaged, profitable organizations both domestically and abroad.
Lizabeth has served on a variety of non-profit boards. More recently, she has been a member of the Trustee board of the Connecticut Science Center since December 2010, serving on the executive committee; and is a member of the Penn State Business School Board since September 2003, most recently serving as Chair. She recently served as a Trustee of the Connecticut Women’s Hall of Fame.
Lizabeth graduated with distinction from The Pennsylvania State University in 1981, was selected as an Alumni Fellow in 2003, and served as the commencement speaker for the business school in 2013. 
Member of the Audit Committee
Member of the Remuneration Committee












